Our Team




Seema Mohanty, Managing Director

	Ms. Mohanty has 15 years of experience in the tax-exempt finance business as both a banker and derivatives marketer. As such, she can provide
	comprehensive advice on the wide range of decisions issuers balance: from bond structures, to credit constructs, to non-traditional products,
	and aggregate debt management.  


	Most recently having joined UBS in January 2007, Ms. Mohanty was a Managing Director and the Head of Derivatives Marketing and Structured Products.
	In this role, she managed a group of 20 professionals responsible for issuer and investor derivatives marketing, quantitative bond analysis and
	lending. Ms. Mohanty oversaw the allocation of a $5 billion lending book, the first at UBS, to provide letters of credit and liquidity facilities
	to tax-exempt clients.  


	Prior to UBS, Ms. Mohanty was a Managing Director and Head of Issuer Derivatives Marketing at Morgan Stanley. She came to Morgan Stanley in 2001
	where she structured, marketed and executed a variety of derivative transactions including interest rate swaps, swaptions, knockout swaps and
	inflation-linked structures. 


	Ms. Mohanty began her career at J.P. Morgan as a banker in municipal finance. She covered a mix of public and private issuers in the infrastructure
	and transportation space. In 1999, Ms. Mohanty joined J.P.Morgan’s Risk Management Marketing Group where she focused on providing structuring ideas
	for tax-exempt clients. She was responsible for developing structuring ideas as well as marketing interest rate derivatives. 

Ms. Mohanty has a BA in Economics from the University of Michigan and an MBA in Finance and Economics from the University of Chicago.

Zoya Gargiulo, Managing Director
Zoya Gargiulo has over 11 years of experience in derivatives, structured products, and tax-exempt bond financing (Tender Option Bond Program (TOB)).

	As a Managing Director and Co-head of Investor Derivatives Marketing at UBS she was responsible for establishing the business strategy,
	infrastructure, risk management and controls, as well as the management of the third-party TOB financing program.


	Prior to joining UBS, Ms. Gargiulo was a Principal at Bank of America Securities where she launched and established institutional investor
	tax-exempt structured products and derivatives business and the third-party TOB program. Within the tax-exempt issuer space she focused on
	structured products such as total return swaps, index put bonds and other direct-lending solutions.


	Ms. Gargiulo started her career at JPMorgan where she spent 8 years as a structured products and derivatives marketer. She has worked on structuring,
	marketing and executing a wide array of interest rate and credit derivatives products for institutional clients investing in tax-exempt securities. Ms. Gargiulo
	was instrumental in building out the third-party TOB book and starting the tax-exempt issuer direct lending solutions business, working with tax-exempt
	issuers on a variety of total return swap transactions and structured bonds. She spent 3 years on the corporate derivatives desk where she provided
	comprehensive risk management solutions to domestic corporate clients. Her work included performing asset liability analyses to determine the clients’
	hedging needs and structuring, marketing and execution of various interest rate and FX derivatives transactions.

Ms. Gargiulo holds an MA in Philosophy from Sofia University and an MBA in Finance from Columbia Business School.

Andrew Rothbaum, Vice President
Andrew Rothbaum worked as an Analyst for Hercules Technology Growth Capital, a publicly traded specialty finance firm that provides venture debt to technology and life sciences companies.  He was involved in all aspects of the deal origination process, including preliminary deal summaries as well as in depth company due diligence for proposals submitted to the Hercules investment committee.  His duties also included monitoring the financial statements of portfolio companies and identifying private equity-backed and debt-financed companies as potential refinancing candidates.
Prior to his time with Hercules, Mr. Rothbaum worked for Wellington Management as part of their Marketing Information Group.  He assisted the team with client interactions, including aiding in the responses of RFPs and populating consultant databases with monthly and quarterly investment returns.  Additionally, he was responsible for updating annual investment returns in accordance with Global Investment Performance Standards.
Mr. Rothbaum also spent time with GE Capital’s private equity group as part of the Financial Planning & Analysis team.  His role involved maintaining the database of all equity investments, as well as working with the investment teams to obtain forecasts used in company planning sessions.
Andrew graduated from Northeastern University with a BS in Business Administration.

Nicholas Dittman,  AnalystPrior to joining Mohanty Gargiulo LLC, Nicholas worked as a Fixed Income Trading Product Analyst for State Street. While in this role he worked with a sales team to handle client analysis requests, including preparation of weekly and monthly investment returns data.  His other projects included working to create presentations for sales pitches, and building an innovative risk analytics program through the online trading portal.


Previously, he worked at Natixis Global Asset Management as a Sales Distribution Analyst. At NGAM, he worked closely with sales representatives to analyze mutual fund transaction data for resolution purposes. Furthermore, he worked on various data integrity projects and provided strategic insight for team meetings.
Nicholas graduated from Northeastern University with a BS in Business Administration.





